RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 46. Maiden Claiming Purse 16600. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OPPO TACO took a quick lead and set a pressured pace, rounded the turn at the rail and dug in all out to just last. S S FOUR QUEENS exchanged contact with Swiss Horizon leaving the gate then gave chase, rounded the turn off the rail, drifted into the lane and dug in under steady encouragement, was gaining quickly on the winner and just missed. TAPTAP gave chase, rounded the turn about the five path and came along to take third inside the sixteenth pole. SWISS HORIZON was squeezed at the break then gave chase, raced near the rail on the turn and showed little in the lane. UNALTERED exchanged contact with Swiss Horizon leaving the gate, gave chase through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the four path and flattened in the lane. GREY FLAMINGO gave chase and faded through the turn. RUMORGOINGAROUND was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: S S Four Queens
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped break,chased inside,off rail turn,drifted,just missed

ENTRY.NAME: Oppo Taco
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,rail turn,just lasted all out

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUBAY pressured the pace and raced at a close disadvantage nearest the rail on the turn, dug in determinedly to take the nod mid-stretch and eked out the advantage over DE'S CASTLE through the final sixteenth. The latter set a pressured pace and contested the edge two deep on the turn, dug in gamely from the head of the lane but reluctantly ceded the final sixteenth. KING OF LUCK chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail, eased out leaving the turn and dug in to take third the final yards. WINDSOR'S STAR gave chase, raced four wide on the turn and was outfinished for third later yards. ROCKING TO HOME chased inside, was ridden apprehensively approaching the five sixteenths pole, resumed full stride past the pole and rounded the turn near the rail, then flattened later yards. BOP ZAPPER pressured the early pace and raced close three wide on the turn, but weakened in the lane. IN HIGH GEAR raced wide and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Rocking to Home
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside,apprehensive ride near 5/16,flattened later yards

ENTRY.NAME: King of Luck
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,rail turn,eased out 1/8,dug in lane,along 3rd late yards

ENTRY.NAME: De's Castle
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,2d turn,game to 1/16,reluctantly ceded

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Claiming Purse 10800. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WATCH ME DISAPPEAR gave chase and rounded the turn off the rail, closed to the lead later yards and drew away nearing the wire. DEVIN ON EARTH took a quick lead and moved to the inside to show the way, came under pressure toward the quarter pole, dug in leaving the turn but was met while flattening stride later yards. MIDNIGHT PASS chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn off the rail, drifted leaving the turn then dueled through the stretch for third. GREAT DEVOTION chased inside, raced at the rail on the turn then outfinished in the stretch duel for third. HOLY HIP came away a bit rank and gave distant early chase, raced near the rail on the turn, angled out entering the stretch and passed rivals. FESSIN UP chased through the backstretch, raced two deep on the turn and showed little in the lane. C TWO gave chase, rounded the turn near the rail and showed little in the lane. CURLIN'S DOVE gave chase and faded in the five path on the turn. HANNAHS RED RUBY was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Watch Me Disappear
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,off rail turn,dug in lane,up later yards,cleared

ENTRY.NAME: Holy Hip
ENTRY.OWNER: C M Racing Stables LLC and Lewis Jalen

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Maiden Claiming Purse 16600. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GEOTHERMAL stalked from the three path on the opening turn, pulled himself to the front past the three eighths pole and was urged away at the rail on the far turn, then kept alert through the stretch. NORLANDER raced in the three path the first turn then eased out entering the backstretch, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and dug in to hold second. CAIRO BREEZE saved early ground, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and ran evenly in the lane. BARRELHOUSE raced off the pace in the three and four paths, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and showed little in the lane. RUSH TO CANDY raced well off the pace in the five and six paths the first turn, left the turn outside and gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the six path and passed rivals widest. HAY DIDDLE DIDDLE steadied lightly on the first turn, picked up the chase from the seven sixteenths pole but flattened off the rail on the far turn. LET'S EAT raced with the pace two deep, dueled leaving the half mile pole but dropped back approaching the quarter and weakened at the rail on the far turn. TO LIVE IS TO LOVE raced with the early pace inside, dueled leaving the half mile pole but weakened at the rail into the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Barrelhouse
ENTRY.OWNER: Warren Andrew N and Warren Rania

ENTRY.NAME: Hay Diddle Diddle
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

ENTRY.NAME: Geothermal
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked 3p,up past 3/8,urged away turn,kept alert lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Claiming Purse 11800. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since September 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. NO WVB CLAUSE.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SULEMAN angled to the inside and rated well off the early pace, started a bid approaching the three eighths pole and steadily improved from that point, raced in the four path on the far turn, dug in leaving the turn and drew clear the final yards. GABRIEL'S WING raced with the pace inside on the first turn, rallied leaving the seven sixteenths pole and took the lead two deep approaching the quarter, contested the edge through the far turn but was caught in late yards. PEAKY BLINKERS settled well off the pace about the four path the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and got up for third the final strides. SCOOTSCOOT raced with the pace two deep and drew briefly clear toward the seven sixteenths pole, was met at the rail approaching the quarter and weakened inside the eighth pole. BUBBA G rounded the first turn in the four path, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened in the lane. CENTRAL PRIDE saved ground on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail on the far turn. AMICALOLA FALLS rounded the first turn in the three and four paths, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole but weakened past the three eighths. SLOE GIN BIZ showed little response through the backstretch.

ENTRY.NAME: Bubba G
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

ENTRY.NAME: Suleman
ENTRY.COMMENT: well off pace inside,bid 3/8,4p far turn,up & clear late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 10800. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALWAYS FORWARD stalked off the rail the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole and raced close off the rail on the far turn then dug in and took over later yards. GOLDEN BLOSSOM rated the pace inside, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn, dug in under steady encouragement leaving the turn but was caught flattening stride later yards. HERECOMES SCARLETT rounded the opening turn about the six path, picked up the chase from the three eighths pole, raced in the four path on the far turn and finished well to take third the final yards. DESTINED TO DANCE raced well off the pace in the five and six paths, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn off the rail and ran evenly in the lane. NELLY TOO settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, angled in leaving the turn but flattened stride the final sixteenth. HEY RIRI raced well off the pace in the three and four paths, gave chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the seven path, left the turn outside and passed rivals. MOONTAP saved ground on the first turn, gave chase from the three eighths pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn. LILY MOR raced off the rail on the opening turn and showed little response through the backstretch. WAVERLEY stalked from the four path the first turn, gave chase into the backstretch but weakened past the five sixteenths pole. DEAREST M. A. stalked in the three path the first turn, challenged toward the three eighths pole but gave way into the far turn. This race was hand timed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 7 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 76. Allowance Purse 27400. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, WAIVER CLAIMING, RESTRICTED OR STATE BRED RACES OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners O f A Race Since September 5 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since August 5 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIMETOGETUP gave chase toward the inside, angled five wide approaching the eighth pole, dug in leaving the turn and steadily improved to get up the final strides. BLACK PANDA pressured the pace and raced close in the three path on the turn, dueled to a brief slim lead in later yards but was caught the final strides. LUNATIC chased through the backstretch, rounded the turn near the rail, was checked and altered course past the eighth pole and finished well to take third the final strides. SHUTUPN'KISSME set a pressured early pace, was met at the rail toward the quarter pole and contested at a close disadvantage through the turn, recovered the nod into the lane but was caught flattening stride later yards. CASTLE LIGHTS pressured the pace and took the lead two deep approaching the quarter pole, contested the edge through the turn but was met into the lane and flattened the final sixteenth. SHE'S A LINO chased, rounded the turn in the four path and ran evenly in the lane. MYGIDGETMARIE chased outside, raced in the six path on the turn and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Black Panda
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace,close 3p turn,brief lead late,caught final strides

ENTRY.NAME: Shutupn'kissme
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace,met rail near 1/4,rail turn,nod 1/8,flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Timetogetup
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,angled 5wd toward 1/8,dug in lane,up final strides

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 8 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 70. Claiming Purse 13700. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON TWO RACES SINCE APRIL 5, 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since April 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A LITTLE BIT CRAZY rated close off the rail the first turn, bid nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail, eased out and took over into the lane, dueled clear past the eighth pole and was steadily handled to hold well. PRACTICALLY THERE saved ground well off the pace on the first turn, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole and steadily improved, rounded the far turn about the three path, closed for second inside the sixteenth pole and finished well. SECRET CASTLE raced with the early pace then stalked in the three path the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and dueled through the stretch for third. BONNIE BLUETOOTH broke awkwardly then bumped outward into China Cat and saved ground on the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and was outfinished in the stretch duel for third. SULTRY SALLY H veered outward at the break and made contact with Bonnie Bluetooth then rated the pace inside, came under pressure toward the five sixteenths pole, contested the advantage at the rail on the far turn but was met into the lane and weakened the final sixteenth. CENTERFOLD ANGEL settled off the rail on the first turn, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path, left the turn outside and showed little more. CHINA CAT was bumped then pinched back at the start and never factored. SUPER WILDCAT became fractious in the paddock then veered out at the break and raced in the four path the first turn, faded past the seven sixteenths pole and was eased the final quarter mile.

ENTRY.NAME: A Little Bit Crazy
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated close,bid near 3/8,rail far turn,up 1/8,cleared,held well

ENTRY.NAME: Centerfold Angel
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Shake and Bake Racing LLC
